cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.SY

This paper is about a statistical mechanics model of deep neural networks and the properties of activation functions. The most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning) as the paper deals with deep neural networks and their performance. The second likely sub-category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as the paper discusses the properties of activation functions in neural networks. The third likely sub-category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as the paper deals with deep learning models. The fourth likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) as the paper discusses the performance of activation functions on a classification task. The fifth likely sub-category is cs.SY (Systems and Control) as the paper discusses the propagation of information through a network.
